 
#	Validation Category	What to Check	Why It Matters	Example Implementation
1	File Type (Extension)	Allow only approved extensions (.jpg, .pdf, .docx, etc.)	Prevents upload of malicious scripts	Whitelist extensions on server side
2	MIME Type Validation	Validate actual MIME type, not just extension	Attackers can rename file extensions	Check Content-Type + server-side MIME inspection
3	File Signature (Magic Number)	Verify file header matches expected format	Detects spoofed file types	Validate magic bytes (e.g., FF D8 FF for JPEG)
4	File Size Limit	Set minimum and maximum size limits	Prevents DoS and storage abuse	Limit to e.g., 5MB per file
5	Maximum Upload Count	Restrict number of files per request/user	Avoid abuse and system overload	Limit to 5 files per upload
6	Filename Sanitization	Remove special characters, path traversal attempts	Prevents directory traversal & injection	Strip ../, null bytes, special chars
7	Rename Uploaded Files	Generate unique server-side filenames	Prevent overwrite attacks	Use UUID or timestamp-based naming
8	Storage Location	Store outside web root	Prevent direct execution	Save in isolated storage bucket/folder
9	Virus/Malware Scan	Scan files before storage/use	Prevent malicious content distribution	Use antivirus APIs (e.g., ClamAV)
10	File Content Validation	Validate structure of file (e.g., valid image format)	Detect embedded malicious payloads	Parse and re-encode images
11	Access Control	Verify user authentication & authorization	Prevent unauthorized uploads	Check user session/token
12	Rate Limiting	Limit upload frequency	Prevent brute-force & abuse	API rate limiting per IP/user
13	Logging & Monitoring	Log upload attempts and failures	Detect suspicious behavior	Maintain audit logs
14	Encryption in Transit	Use HTTPS	Prevent man-in-the-middle attacks	Enforce TLS
15	Encryption at Rest	Encrypt stored files	Protect sensitive data	Use encrypted storage (e.g., S3 SSE)
16	File Parsing Safeguards	Use safe libraries to process files	Avoid parser vulnerabilities	Keep libraries updated
17	Error Handling	Return generic error messages	Prevent information leakage	Avoid exposing stack traces
18	Content Security Policy (CSP)	Restrict file execution	Prevent XSS from uploaded files	Use CSP headers
19	Cross-Origin Restrictions	Validate CORS policy	Prevent cross-site upload abuse	Configure strict CORS rules
20	Backup & Retention Policy	Define file retention rules	Compliance & storage management	Auto-delete after X days
